A ‘quantum leap’ has been made in encryption technology that could help securely transfer sensitive data.

The technology - known as Quantum Key Distribution (QKD) – delivers private data using the smallest possible packets of light.

Data could include encrypted personal information, such as patient health records between hospitals, or payments between credit card providers and online retailers.

