The receiver detects the photons as 0s and 1s but not which base. So it randomly chooses which base it will detect and records the values and bases.

Once all the information has been received, the receiver tells the transmitter which bases it detected and the transmitter reveals which were right and wrong.

The receiver rejects all wrong detection events – leaving just the correct ones.

Armed with this information, it can create the key to first encrypt and subsequently decrypt and unlock the data.

